> From: "librarian" <librarian(-at-)uulibrary.com>
> > If you paste your multi-line URL in at www.tinyurl.com, it will spit out a
> > very short version that anyone can cut and paste very easily.
>
> I understand that one drawback of this is that TinyURL links are short-lived
> compared to listserv archive storage.  After a short time, the link expires
> and the archived message looses some of its usefulness.

This is indeed a drawback although the life-span of most web page links is
not usually very long either.  Discretion would be needed. If the link is
important and to a permanent site then the full link would be better.

